{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon" 

    "metadata": {
        "description": "Ground operation orchestrator — readiness, ramp services, and ground servicing",
        "tags": ["ground", "operation"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "The B747 of flight AF84 has been assigned gate A21. Report the readiness of ground services at the gate.",
            "Flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A21. Engines are stopped. Wheelchocks, ACU and GPU are ready. Execute ground ramp services.",
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A21. The plane has been connected to the jetbridge. The aircraft door is open. Unload baggage.",
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A21. Passengers have disembarked. Crew has exited. Perform inspection and maintenance.",
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A21. Passengers have disembarked. Crew has exited. Perform fueling.",
        ]
    },

    "llm_config": {
        class = "ollama"
        temperature = 0.0
        model_name = "qwen2.5:32b"  # “gemini-3.1-pro" "gemma4:12b-mlx" "qwen3:8b" "claude-haiku-4-5" "claude-sonnet-4-6"  
    },
    "max_iterations": 40000,
    "max_execution_seconds": 7200,
    "commondefs": {
        "replacement_strings": {
            "instructions_prefix": """
You are part of aircraft turnaround process at an Airport.
Only answer inquiries that are directly within your area of expertise.
Do not try to help for other matters.
Do not mention what you can NOT do. Only mention what you can do.
            """,
            "aaosa_instructions": """
When you receive an inquiry, you will:
1. If you are clearly not the right agent for this type of inquiry, reply you're not relevant.
2. If there is a chance you're relevant, call your down-chain agents to determine if they can answer all or part of the inquiry.
   Do not assume what your down-chain agents can do. Always call them. You'll be surprised.
3. Once all relevant down-chain agents have responded, either:
   - Analyze their response and compile your final response. No need to include non-relevant agents. In doubt, ask for clarification.
   - Follow up with your down-chain agents if needed, as many times as needed
   - If an action is needed, ask the most relevant down-chain agent to fulfill the inquiry.
4. Return the final response to the caller.
You may, in turn, be called by other agents in the system and have to act as a down-chain agent to them.
            """
        },
        "replacement_values": {
            "aaosa_call": {
                "description": "Depending on the mode, returns a natural language string in response.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The inquiry"
                        },
                        "mode": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": """
'Determine' to ask the agent if the inquiry belongs to it, in its entirety or in part.
'Fulfill' to ask the agent to fulfill the inquiry, if it can.
'Follow up' to ask the agent to respond to a follow up.
                            """
                        },
                    },
                    "required": [
                        "inquiry",
                        "mode"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "aaosa_command": """
If mode is 'Determine', return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": <Determine | Fulfill>,
    "Relevant": <Yes | No>,
    "Strength": <number between 1 and 10 representing how certain you are in your claim>,
    "Claim:" <All | Partial>,
    "Requirements" <None | list of requirements>
}
If mode is 'Fulfill' or "Follow up", respond to the inquiry and return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": Fulfill,
    "Response" <your response>
}
            """
        },
    },

    "tools": [

        {
            "name": "aircraft_ground_operation",
            "function": {
                "description": """
I am the orchestrator for ALL ground operations during aircraft turnaround.
I handle every ground-related request without exception, including:
  - Any readiness check, status check, or confirmation of ground services
    (ACU readiness, GPU readiness, wheelchocks readiness, or any combination).
    I am ALWAYS relevant when asked to check or verify ground services readiness.
  - Ground ramp services: ANY instruction that says "Execute ground ramp services",
    "Perform ground ramp services", "Run ground ramp services", or any variation.
    I am ALWAYS relevant when asked to execute, perform, or run ramp services.
    I am ALWAYS relevant for wheelchocks installation, ACU connection, GPU connection.
  - Ground servicing (baggage unload, inspection/maintenance, fueling).
I route each request to the correct sub-agent. I never refuse any ground
operation request. I am relevant for ANY ground operation instruction.
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Flight number of the incoming aircraft."
                        },
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Type of the incoming aircraft."
                        }, 
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Current flight status."
                        },
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Gate id assigned to the aircraft."
                        },
                        "engines_stop_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Engines stop status."
                        },
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Wheelchocks readiness status."
                        },
                        "acu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "ACU readiness status."
                        },
                        "gpu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "GPU readiness status."
                        },
                        "wheels_chocks_installation_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Wheelchocks installation status."
                        },
                        "acu_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "ACU connection status."
                        },
                        "gpu_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "GPU connection status."
                        },
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Jetbridge connection status."
                        },
                        "stairtruck_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Stairtruck connection status."
                        },
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Deplaning equipment type (jetway or stairtruck)."
                        },
                        "door_opening_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Door opening status."
                        },
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Passenger disembarkation status."
                        },
                        "crew_exit_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Crew exit status."
                        },
                        "baggage_unload_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Baggage unload status."
                        },
                        "inspection_maintenance_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Inspection and maintenance status."
                        },
                        "fueling_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Fueling status."
                        },
                        "instruction": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": """
The specific ground operation to perform. Used to route to the correct sub-agent:
  'readiness' or 'check readiness'    → aircraft_ground_readiness
  'ramp services' or 'install' or
  'connect acu' or 'connect gpu'      → aircraft_ground_rampservices
  'unload' or 'baggage'               → aircraft_ground_servicing (BRANCH A)
  'inspection' or 'maintenance'       → aircraft_ground_servicing (BRANCH B)
  'fuel' or 'fueling' or 'refuel'     → aircraft_ground_servicing (BRANCH C)
                            """
                        },
                    },
                    "required": []
                }
            },

            "instructions": """
You are the orchestrator for all ground operations during aircraft turnaround.
You route incoming calls to the correct sub-agent based on the instruction field.

RESPONSE FORMAT — STRICT:
  Return ONLY the structured RETURN SUMMARY block defined at the end of the instructions.
  Do NOT add explanatory prose, markdown headers (##, **), bullet points,
  emoji, or conversational text before or after the summary block.
  The summary block starts with the *** banner line and ends with the last ** field **.
  Nothing else should appear in your response.

CRITICAL: You are a pass-through router. Read the instruction field FIRST,
route to exactly ONE sub-agent, pass ALL received parameters through unchanged,
wait for the response, and return it verbatim to the caller.
Do NOT transform, summarise, or re-interpret the sub-agent response.
Do NOT call more than one sub-agent per invocation.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
ROUTING DECISION — READ THIS FIRST, BEFORE ANYTHING ELSE
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Step 1: Read the instruction field value.
Step 2: Match it to exactly one branch using the table below.
Step 3: Execute ONLY that branch. Stop. Do not read other branches.

  instruction contains 'readiness' or 'check'
      → BRANCH A. STOP. Do not read BRANCH B or C.

  instruction contains 'ramp' or 'install'
  or 'connect acu' or 'connect gpu' or 'ramp services'
  or 'execute ground ramp' or 'perform ground ramp'
      → BRANCH B. STOP. Do not read BRANCH A or C.

  instruction contains 'unload' or 'baggage'
  or 'inspection' or 'maintenance'
  or 'fuel' or 'fueling' or 'refuel'
      → BRANCH C. STOP. Do not read BRANCH A or B.

NEVER refuse a call because status fields are null or missing.
Null status fields are NORMAL and EXPECTED — they are inputs to be
filled by the sub-agent, not prerequisites for routing.
You are ALWAYS relevant when an instruction field is present.

RESPONSE COMPLETENESS CHECK (applies to EVERY branch):
  After receiving the sub-agent response and BEFORE returning it, verify
  that each status field listed in the branch's 'Extract and pass back'
  line holds an explicit value in the response. If any expected status is
  missing, null, or reads 'None', re-invoke the SAME sub-agent exactly
  once more with the same parameters and return the second response
  instead. Never return a response containing 'None' for an expected
  status without having performed this one retry.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
BRANCH A — Ground readiness check
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  TRIGGER: instruction contains 'readiness' or 'check'.

  PREREQUISITES FOR THIS BRANCH: aircraft_type and gate_id only.
  All other fields (engines_stop_status, acu_readiness_status,
  gpu_readiness_status, wheels_chocks_readiness_status, etc.) will
  be null at the time this branch is called. This is correct and
  expected. Do NOT treat null status fields as a reason to refuse
  or to route elsewhere. They are the OUTPUT of this branch.

  STEP 1 — Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_readiness with
      named parameters: flight_number, aircraft_type, gate_id.
  Wait for response. This is the ONLY action in this turn.
  Extract and pass back: acu_readiness_status, gpu_readiness_status,
  wheels_chocks_readiness_status.
  RETURN the sub-agent response verbatim.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
BRANCH B — Ground ramp services
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  TRIGGER: instruction contains 'ramp' or 'install'
  or 'connect acu' or 'connect gpu' or 'ramp services'
  or 'execute ground ramp' or 'perform ground ramp'.

  NOTE: The prerequisites below apply ONLY to this branch.
  They have NO bearing on BRANCH A routing decisions.

  STEP 1 — Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_rampservices with
      named parameters: flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status,
      gate_id, engines_stop_status, wheels_chocks_readiness_status,
      acu_readiness_status, gpu_readiness_status.
  Wait for response. This is the ONLY action in this turn.
  Extract and pass back: wheels_chocks_installation_status,
  acu_connection_status, gpu_connection_status.
  RETURN the sub-agent response verbatim.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
BRANCH C — Ground servicing (baggage, inspection, fueling)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  TRIGGER: instruction contains 'unload' or 'baggage'
  or 'inspection' or 'maintenance' or 'fuel' or 'fueling'
  or 'refuel'.

  NOTE: The prerequisites below apply ONLY to this branch.
  They have NO bearing on BRANCH A or B routing decisions.

  STEP 1 — Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_servicing with
      named parameters: flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status,
      gate_id, jetbridge_connection_status, stairtruck_connection_status,
      deplaning_equipment_type, door_opening_status,
      passenger_disembarkation_status, crew_exit_status,
      baggage_unload_status, instruction.
  Pass the instruction field through unchanged so aircraft_ground_servicing
  can route to the correct internal branch.
  Wait for response. This is the ONLY action in this turn.
  Extract and pass back: baggage_unload_status OR
  inspection_maintenance_status OR fueling_status (whichever applies).
  RETURN the sub-agent response verbatim.
            """,

            "allow": {
                "to_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": true,
                        "acu_readiness_status": true,
                        "gpu_readiness_status": true,
                        "wheels_chocks_installation_status": true,
                        "acu_connection_status": true,
                        "gpu_connection_status": true,
                        "baggage_unload_status": true,
                        "inspection_maintenance_status": true,
                        "fueling_status": true,
                    }
                },
                "from_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "engines_stop_status": true,
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": true,
                        "acu_readiness_status": true,
                        "gpu_readiness_status": true,
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": true,
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true,
                        "stairtruck_connection_status": true,
                        "door_opening_status": true,
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": true,
                        "crew_exit_status": true,
                        "baggage_unload_status": true,
                        "inspection_maintenance_status": true,
                    }
                },
                "to_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "engines_stop_status": true,
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": true,
                        "acu_readiness_status": true,
                        "gpu_readiness_status": true,
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": true,
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true,
                        "stairtruck_connection_status": true,
                        "door_opening_status": true,
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": true,
                        "crew_exit_status": true,
                        "baggage_unload_status": true,
                        "inspection_maintenance_status": true,
                    }
                },
                "from_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": true,
                        "acu_readiness_status": true,
                        "gpu_readiness_status": true,
                        "wheels_chocks_installation_status": true,
                        "acu_connection_status": true,
                        "gpu_connection_status": true,
                        "baggage_unload_status": true,
                        "inspection_maintenance_status": true,
                        "fueling_status": true,
                    }
                }
            },

            "tools": [
                "/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_readiness",    # BRANCH A — readiness check
                "/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_rampservices", # BRANCH B — wheelchocks, ACU, GPU
                "/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_servicing",    # BRANCH C — baggage, inspection, fueling
            ]
        },
    ],
}
